# Keep the Docker build context lean.
#
# The watcher build (`docker build -f watchers/.../Dockerfile .`)
# needs:
#   - Workspace Cargo.toml + Cargo.lock
#   - All Rust-crate Cargo.toml files (for workspace resolution)
#   - The watcher crate source + its dependencies' source
#
# It does NOT need: build artifacts, .NET projects, test fixtures,
# the vendored Neo / Neo-zkvm submodules (the watcher crate doesn't
# depend on them), the docs site, the SDK web app, etc.

# Build artifacts.
target/
**/target/
# Note: `**/bin/` would strip Rust's `src/bin/` source dirs (cargo
# binary entrypoints live at `<crate>/src/bin/<name>.rs`). Allowlist
# Rust src/bin/ back in. The intent of `**/bin/` is .NET build
# output (which lives at `<project>/bin/`, not `src/bin/`).
**/bin/
!**/src/bin/
!**/src/bin/**
**/obj/
**/dist/
**/node_modules/
artifacts/
out/
TestResults/
coverage/

# Git + IDE state — large + irrelevant to the build.
.git/
.gitignore
.vscode/
.idea/
.vs/
*.swp
*.tmp
*.log
.DS_Store

# Vendored submodules under external/. Most aren't needed by the
# watcher's Rust build, but `bridge/neo-zkvm-guest` (a workspace
# member) has a path dep on `external/neo-zkvm/crates/neo-vm-guest`,
# so cargo workspace metadata resolution requires that one to be
# present. Exclude the others (~325 MB combined).
external/neo/
external/neo-devpack-dotnet/
external/neo-riscv-vm/
external/foreign-contracts/

# .NET artifacts that occasionally land in source paths.
*.user
*.suo
*.dll
*.pdb
*.exe

# mdBook output.
book/

# Docker assets themselves don't need to be in the context.
**/Dockerfile
.dockerignore
